I'm going to go through these
topics, you can just take a

00:09:16.820 --> 00:09:19.090
quick glance at them.
 

00:09:19.090 --> 00:09:27.149
They are basically the details
of what I've just adumbrated,

00:09:27.149 --> 00:09:33.980
and the last of them is the
case for your final.

00:09:33.980 --> 00:09:43.812
Okay capital,
capital is accumulated wealth

00:09:43.812 --> 00:09:49.899
reproductively deployed.
 

00:09:49.899 --> 00:09:53.120
It can take the form of
cultivated land,

00:09:53.120 --> 00:09:57.605
it can take the form of seed
corn, it can take the form of

00:09:57.605 --> 00:10:02.376
factory machinery,
it can take the form of stock

00:10:02.376 --> 00:10:07.089
certificates,
it can take the form of

00:10:07.089 --> 00:10:11.746
educated people;
indeed, in a very real sense

00:10:11.746 --> 00:10:16.313
you are in the process of
capital formation during your

00:10:16.313 --> 00:10:19.019
years as university students.
 

00:10:19.019 --> 00:10:23.090
You will be an embodiment of
capital,

00:10:23.090 --> 00:10:27.611
and indeed, capital of a high
order when you finish Yale

00:10:27.611 --> 00:10:30.820
College or the School of
Management,

00:10:30.820 --> 00:10:35.332
or the law school,
or whatever may be your last

00:10:35.332 --> 00:10:36.019
stop.
 

00:10:36.019 --> 00:10:41.398
Capitalism, on the other hand,
is the name that socialists

00:10:41.398 --> 00:10:46.210
gave to a whole bunch of things
they didn't like.

00:10:46.210 --> 00:10:51.668
Private businesses that,
in their view,

00:10:51.668 --> 00:10:54.998
exploited labor,
in their view despoiled the

00:10:54.998 --> 00:10:58.779
environment,
in their view desanctified

00:10:58.779 --> 00:11:02.509
historical and religious
tradition,

00:11:02.509 --> 00:11:05.808
and there is no inventor of
capitalism.

00:11:05.808 --> 00:11:09.971
Adam Smith didn't use the term,
Adam Smith didn't even like

00:11:09.971 --> 00:11:13.517
joint stock corporations;
he thought they generally

00:11:13.517 --> 00:11:17.727
didn't work well,
but it is an organic system,

00:11:17.727 --> 00:11:23.903
which develops over time,
and as Hayek and Schumpeter and

00:11:23.903 --> 00:11:29.679
others point out to us,
is capable of self-modification

00:11:29.679 --> 00:11:31.090
through time.
 

00:11:31.090 --> 00:11:34.860
Marx's historicist theory of
this,

00:11:34.860 --> 00:11:39.210
and we did a whole lecture on
this in September,

00:11:39.210 --> 00:11:43.714
with the idea that capitalism
always turns toward monopolies

00:11:43.714 --> 00:11:46.538
that capital becomes too
abundant,

00:11:46.538 --> 00:11:49.110
and the rate of return on it
falls with time,

00:11:49.110 --> 00:11:54.048
that the working class is
eventually starved out,

00:11:54.048 --> 00:11:58.235
eviscerated to use the term,
the inevitable revolution in

00:11:58.235 --> 00:12:00.480
advanced capitalist systems.
 

00:12:00.480 --> 00:12:04.975
The places the revolution
occurred were always in the

00:12:04.975 --> 00:12:10.509
least advanced market societies,
places like the Soviet Union.

00:12:10.509 --> 00:12:14.181
The theory of a universal
class, that once the working

00:12:14.181 --> 00:12:18.200
class captures society there
will be no class below it,

00:12:18.200 --> 00:12:22.188
and therefore,
no possibility of conflict and

00:12:22.188 --> 00:12:29.759
exploitation,
the withering away of the state.

00:12:29.759 --> 00:12:34.558
Well here are the places where
the revolution occurred in red,

00:12:34.558 --> 00:12:38.769
and it occurred in almost all
of them because the capitalist

00:12:38.769 --> 00:12:41.980
order was not developing and not
maturing,

00:12:41.980 --> 00:12:50.394
rather than that it was
developing and had exhausted

00:12:50.394 --> 00:12:51.879
itself.
 

00:12:51.879 --> 00:12:59.220
The withering away of the state
takes awhile.

00:12:59.220 --> 00:13:01.798
This is from the Communist
Manifesto,

00:13:01.798 --> 00:13:04.019
and this is where he gets it
right.

00:13:04.019 --> 00:13:07.947
The notion that the
bourgeoisie, that is

00:13:07.947 --> 00:13:10.890
capitalists,
cannot exist without

00:13:10.890 --> 00:13:14.755
constitution--constantly
revolutionizing the process of

00:13:14.755 --> 00:13:18.259
production,
that the conservation of old

00:13:18.259 --> 00:13:23.120
ways of doing things was
characteristic of every previous

00:13:23.120 --> 00:13:26.678
economic system but not of
capitalism.

00:13:26.678 --> 00:13:32.379
"All that is solid melts
into air.

00:13:32.379 --> 00:13:37.360
So the flat part of this is
pre-capitalism,

00:13:37.360 --> 00:13:44.144
this is the Angus-Madison Curve
that Clark in his Farewell to

00:13:44.144 --> 00:13:48.129
Alms uses as his thesis
again,

00:13:48.129 --> 00:13:49.629
and again, and again.
 

00:13:49.629 --> 00:13:52.110
And the upturn corresponds to
the capitalist era.

00:13:52.110 --> 00:13:56.697
Now it also corresponds to the
era of intensive use of fossil

00:13:56.697 --> 00:13:57.308
fuels.
 

00:13:57.308 --> 00:14:01.870
It also corresponds to the era
of radical urbanization,

00:14:01.870 --> 00:14:06.596
and it also corresponds to a
period of extraordinarily fast

00:14:06.596 --> 00:14:10.528
technological innovation,
and you can say that I give

00:14:10.528 --> 00:14:14.374
capitalism too much credit,
and I'll settle for agreeing

00:14:14.374 --> 00:14:15.190
with that.
 

00:14:15.190 --> 00:14:19.399
But I will also say that
capitalism is a--

00:14:19.399 --> 00:14:21.643
has within it,
endogenously,

00:14:21.643 --> 00:14:25.548
enormous incentives for
continuous technological

00:14:25.548 --> 00:14:29.787
innovation and for the rapid
deployment of desirable

00:14:29.787 --> 00:14:39.596
technologies,
and in that way it differs from

00:14:39.596 --> 00:14:44.590
all other systems.
 

00:14:44.590 --> 00:14:48.083
Capitalism during its rule of
scarce 100 years has created

00:14:48.083 --> 00:14:51.823
more massive and more colossal
productive forces than have all

00:14:51.823 --> 00:14:53.970
preceding generations together.
 

00:14:53.970 --> 00:14:55.830
That's a true statement.
 

00:14:55.830 --> 00:15:02.272
It was made in the winter of
1847-1848 and it was arguably

00:15:02.272 --> 00:15:08.149
true then, it is vastly more
obviously true today.

00:15:08.149 --> 00:15:11.580
That in roughly ten
generations, maybe twelve

00:15:11.580 --> 00:15:15.779
generations,
capitalism has created more

00:15:15.779 --> 00:15:22.291
total wealth and total spending
power than all the economic

00:15:22.291 --> 00:15:28.690
systems which occupied human
history before that time.

